<subSubSection id="56781A55834BCA818D94091D8F9FACC3" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="433BDA53A031B0D04CBBE127E219A962" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90727AB56FE614413089EB397AC380F4" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Among the strongly depressed, metallic species lacking a sutural stria, 
<taxonomicName id="3D148A141E3E1C550AD92406469A23FA" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia nebulosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">Baconia nebulosa</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by its small size, and by its short, wide head and peculiar, mostly concealed mandibles (Fig. 9E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB4D4C3264C8A9A149960DBC268B1C2F" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1F88112F0C5180F24D07D1F681CC2515" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B33F1841159D4941C4A0F0C65AF511E" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
The name of this species means 
<normalizedToken id="5086A5D516CF567B6A3926379383C9ED" originalValue="‘foggy’">'foggy'</normalizedToken>
, referring mainly to the fact that it was collected by fogging the canopy of lowland forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
